WEBVTT

00:01:57.355 --> 00:02:00.705
to commit more than half
their fortunes to philanthropy.

00:02:01.113 --> 00:02:03.327
(TED Talk) BG: The world
is a far better place

00:02:03.351 --> 00:02:05.922
because of the philanthropists of the past

00:02:05.946 --> 00:02:08.887
and the US tradition here,
which is the strongest,

00:02:08.911 --> 00:02:10.442
is the envy of the world.

00:02:10.466 --> 00:02:13.720
I do think philanthropy is going to grow

00:02:13.744 --> 00:02:15.149
and take some of these things

00:02:15.173 --> 00:02:17.983
governments are just not good
at working on and discovering,

00:02:18.007 --> 00:02:20.399
and shine some light
in the right direction.

00:02:20.942 --> 00:02:24.695
CA: Of course, there are plenty
of questions and controversies

00:02:24.719 --> 00:02:27.243
swirling in philanthropy in general.

00:02:27.267 --> 00:02:31.130
And especially when it comes to
how billionaires seek to change the world.